node.text:
I used to give myself a LOT of credit for my marriage to @lisabilyeu. I thought, damn, man... I’m GOOD at this. And then it hit me... the statement that 80% of a successful relationship is selection. 

You have to choose the right partner. A high functioning relationship will be the greatest joy of your life - something well worth great sacrifice to protect and nurture. But a dysfunctional relationship will completely dismantle your life. 

Before you embark on the journey of rebuilding, make sure that you’re rebuilding the right relationship. If this is the right relationship - amazing! Go on in repairing. But, man... if it’s not. If you’re in a relationship with someone who has contempt for you or you have contempt for them, I advise you to face head on that this may not be the right relationship to save. 

Just keep in mind, your partner is looking at you the same way. You both have to be worth fighting for. 

For anyone out there struggling, I’m sending you good vibes and hoping that you can build a better situation for yourself - with your current partner or without them. 

But don’t think your worth is tied up in making it work. You’ve only got one shot at life, so make sure you’re building something that lifts you and those around you up. I’m sending all the love in the world. 

For @lisabilyeu ’s take on this be sure to subscribe to our Relationship Theory YouTube channel. We go deep on all of this stuff. Link in bio.

node.title: Is It Time To Dump Your Partner

node.text:
On this week’s episode of Health Theory, join me as I reveal the daily habits that help me perform at an elite level. 

If you have followed me for any amount of time, you have likely heard me say action cures all. Since starting Healthy Theory, I have interviewed over 90 specialists and experts about everything from brain cognition, to gut microbiome, to reverse aging. Information is meant to be put into action, so today I am sharing with you what my daily routine consists of at the moment. This episode is Health Theory In Action.

To watch the entire episode on your favorite platform, click the link in bio.

node.text:
Is it a bird? Is it a plane? No, it’s a man putting his whole heart into one moment! 

You may not recognize him, or even care for this sport, but what is undeniable when you look at a person striving to be superhuman, is the complete and utter dedication it takes. 

Take a moment and think about the last time you poured yourself into a single instance with complete abandon. How did it feel to give it your all?

Shout out @_infinite_tucker for his winning Superman dive 🔥 via @sportscenter @secnetwork @aggietrk

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tom Bilyeu on August 04, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text that says 'CONSIDER EVERY DIFFICULTY AN OPPORTUNITY TO GROW AND IMPROVE NOT PROOF THAT YOU'RE A MORON. Ruaer'.

node.text:
You get what you look for.

If you’re only looking for proof that you’re a moron, that’s all you will find.

If instead, you look for opportunities to grow and improve, you will.

May be a black-and-white image of text that says 'Who you could be 5 years from now @TOMBILYEU If you don't know EXACTLY who you want to be and what you want to be doing in 5 years, you're already doing it. Let that sink in. If you don't know who you're trying to grow into, you're ALREADY who you're going to be in 5 years. node.text: Decide who you want to be. Until you do that, you’re stuck by default.

node.text:
I used to give myself a LOT of credit for my marriage to @lisabilyeu. I thought, damn, man... I’m GOOD at this. And then it hit me... the statement that 80% of a successful relationship is selection. 

You have to choose the right partner. A high functioning relationship will be the greatest joy of your life - something well worth great sacrifice to protect and nurture. But a dysfunctional relationship will completely dismantle your life. 

Before you embark on the journey of rebuilding, make sure that you’re rebuilding the right relationship. If this is the right relationship - amazing! Go on in repairing. But, man... if it’s not. If you’re in a relationship with someone who has contempt for you or you have contempt for them, I advise you to face head on that this may not be the right relationship to save. 

Just keep in mind, your partner is looking at you the same way. You both have to be worth fighting for. 

For anyone out there struggling, I’m sending you good vibes and hoping that you can build a better situation for yourself - with your current partner or without them. 

But don’t think your worth is tied up in making it work. You’ve only got one shot at life, so make sure you’re building something that lifts you and those around you up. I’m sending all the love in the world. 

For @lisabilyeu ’s take on this be sure to subscribe to our Relationship Theory YouTube channel. We go deep on all of this stuff. Link in bio.

node.text: Now that we have that out in the open, what are you going to do about it? How will you take control of your life? No one is coming to save you, so it is on you!

Hindsight is 20/20, but successful people have excellent vision for the now and even better vision on the future. You must become extremely intentional with what you want your future to be! #ImpactTheoryUniversity

node.text: I love this quote so much, because it is so damn true. It's all about how you feel about yourself when you're by yourself. It's about service and falling in love with pushing yourself past the breaking point to get better every damn day. Ironically enough, fulfillment is born out of suffering with a purpose.
